The paper presents a tool for transforming the definition of a function into a simplified definition, providing a proof of equivalence between the old and new functions. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category, which deals with formal methods and logic-based approaches to computer science. 

The paper also mentions program transformation in synthesis and verification, which suggests that it could also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. 

The tool is designed to generate termination and guard proofs for the new function, which suggests that it could also belong to the Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) sub-category. 

Finally, the paper mentions that examples are used to illustrate the utility of the tool, which suggests that it could also belong to the Symbolic Computation (cs.SC) sub-category, which deals with the use of symbolic methods and algorithms in computer science.
